        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Track S tiles and blanks first:</span> These are the most impactful tiles to track. Knowing if they're still in play changes your defensive/offensive posture completely.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Count vowels vs consonants remaining:</span> If the bag is vowel-heavy, keep consonants when exchanging. If consonant-heavy, keep your vowels. This simple ratio check improves exchange decisions enormously.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use tracking for exchange decisions:</span> Before exchanging, check what's left. If you need an S but all 4 are played, don't exchange hoping to draw one — it's impossible.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Update every turn without exception:</span> Skipping tracking for "just one turn" means losing information permanently. Be disciplined — update after every play, yours and your opponent's.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">In the endgame, calculate before playing:</span> When the bag is empty, take your time. Count tiles, deduce opponent's rack, then choose the play that guarantees the best outcome given what they hold.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

